<sect1 id="Day">
  <title><emphasis role="bold">Day</emphasis></title>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">STD.Date.Day<indexterm>
      <primary>STD.Date.Day</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>Date.Day</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis> <emphasis>date</emphasis> <emphasis
  role="bold">)</emphasis></para>

  <informaltable colsep="0" frame="none" rowsep="0">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="80.50pt" />

      <colspec />

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><emphasis>date</emphasis></entry>

          <entry>A date value in the Date_t format.</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry>Return:</entry>

          <entry>Day returns an INTEGER value in the range of 1 through
          31.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold">Day</emphasis> function returns the Day
  number from the <emphasis>date</emphasis> value.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <programlisting format="linespecific">IMPORT STD;
UNSIGNED4 MyDate := 20120101;   //January 1, 2012
  
D := STD.Date.Day(MyDate);
    //D contains 1, representing the first of the month
  </programlisting>

  <para></para>
</sect1>
